BT 1 0 0 1 0 52.3 Tm 12.2 TL /F2 8.7 Tf .090196 .12549 .2 rg (Three call styles) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf  T* /F2 8.7 Tf (Result-first:) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf ( use methods such as ) Tj /F3 8.7 Tf (write_result\(\)) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf (, ) Tj /F3 8.7 Tf (read_result\(\)) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf (, and ) Tj /F3 8.7 Tf (rank_trace_result\(\)) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf ( in long-running AI services.) Tj  T* /F2 8.7 Tf (Direct-value:) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf ( use ) Tj /F3 8.7 Tf (read_value\(\)) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf (, ) Tj /F3 8.7 Tf (read_text\(\)) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf (, and typed loaders when missing/corrupt data should be exceptional.) Tj  T* /F2 8.7 Tf (Prepare / commit / replay:) Tj /F1 8.7 Tf ( CSV and semantic contracts make mutation authority explicit. Prepare is generally read-only; commit) Tj T* (persists; replay detects drift.) Tj T* ET
Q
Q
